    {
      "parameters": {
        "text": "={{ JSON.stringify($json) }}",
        "attributes": {
          "attributes": [
            {
              "name": "normalized_first_name",
              "description": "First name, properly capitalized. \"\" if unknown."
            },
            {
              "name": "normalized_last_name",
              "description": "Last name, properly capitalized. \"\" if unknown."
            },
            {
              "name": "company_name",
              "description": "Company; infer from email domain if blank; \"\" for personal providers"
            },
            {
              "name": "company_domain",
              "description": "Lowercased domain from the email; \"\" for personal providers."
            },
            {
              "name": "industry",
              "description": "Best-guess industry; \"unknown\" if not inferable."
            },
            {
              "name": "seniority",
              "description": "One of: c_level, vp, director, manager, individual_contributor, unknown."
            },
            {
              "name": "segment",
              "description": "Short persona label e.g. agency_owner, smb_marketer; \"unknown\" if unclear."
            },
            {
              "name": "summary",
              "description": "One sentence about who this contact is."
            },
            {
              "name": "data_quality_score",
              "type": "number",
              "description": "0–100 integer, quality of the ORIGINAL record."
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {
          "systemPromptTemplate": "=You are a CRM data-hygiene assistant. You clean and enrich ONE contact record using\nONLY the information provided plus what can be directly inferred from the email address.\n\nRules:\n1. Never invent facts you cannot infer. No fake phone numbers, no guessed real companies\n   beyond what the email domain tells you.\n2. Proper-case names: \"john smith\" -> \"John Smith\", \"SARA\" -> \"Sara\".\n3. If company is blank, infer it from the email domain (e.g. john@acmewidgets.com ->\n   \"Acme Widgets\"). Leave company blank for personal/free email providers.\n4. company_domain = the part after \"@\" in the email, lowercased — BUT return an empty\n   string (\"\") when the domain is a personal/free email provider. Treat these as personal:\n   gmail.com, googlemail.com, yahoo.com, ymail.com, hotmail.com, outlook.com, live.com,\n   msn.com, icloud.com, me.com, mac.com, aol.com, proton.me, protonmail.com, gmx.com,\n   zoho.com. For a personal provider, BOTH company_name AND company_domain MUST be \"\".\n5. seniority: infer from job title, exactly one of:\n   c_level, vp, director, manager, individual_contributor, unknown.\n   Mapping:\n   - c_level: CEO, CTO, CFO, COO, any \"Chief ...\" title, Founder, Co-Founder, President, Owner.\n   - vp: \"VP\", \"Vice President\", \"SVP\", \"EVP\".\n   - director: \"Director\", or any \"Head of ...\" title.\n   - manager: \"Manager\", \"Lead\", \"Supervisor\".\n   - individual_contributor: specialist, coordinator, associate, analyst, engineer,\n     representative, or any title with no leadership indicator.\n   - unknown: only when the job title is blank or genuinely unclassifiable.\n6. industry / segment: best guess from company + title; use \"unknown\" if not inferable.\n7. summary: one sentence describing who this contact is, based only on given data.\n8. data_quality_score: integer 0-100 reflecting how COMPLETE and CLEAN the ORIGINAL\n   record was (full name + company + title + valid business email = high; mostly blank = low).\n9. For anything you genuinely cannot determine, return an empty string (\"\") — except\n   industry/seniority/segment which use \"unknown\"."
        }
      },
